(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Modern Physics.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind the main ideas and methods) Tj
T*
(involved in Modern Physics.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct physical reasoning process step by step instead of jumping to the) Tj
T*
(answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on a simple classroom example involving Modern Physics.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in the main ideas and methods involved in Modern Physics that) Tj
T*
(the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Modern Physics step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on short questions that build confidence) Tj
T*
(in Modern Physics.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
